It can't be much different than the aftermarket gauge:

http://egauges.com/pdf/vdo/0-515-012-123.pdf

> Am I correct in assuming this is a powered gauge? I kinda expected  
> it would have had a self-powered thermistor like the CHT does.

Yes. The resistance changes with temperature. Usually the NTC  
thermistor variety.

> And finally: Does this gauge care how much wire is between it and  
> the sender?

Nope, the resistance of the sender far exceeds the resistance of the  
wiring.

